<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-18-1163 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Mobil Oil Refinery Woerth presents itself in a more modern and morecompetetive condition following its extensive modernization and overhaulin September 1987. The refining efficiency has been increased by improvementof overall yield-structure and energy utilization of both 'key units'crude oil distillation and catalytic cracker (FCC). The steps taken toreduce the emission of pollutants will make an important contributionto protecting the environment. This is essential if the refinery is tobe able to hold its own in the face of environmental legislation thatis necessarily growing more stringent all the time.</TEXT></DOC>